Description: Shoulder sherd of East Greek (North Ionian) black-figured pottery closed vessel (dinos?); pale orange clay, porous surface; interior reserved; exterior: cream slip, glaze fired orange; key maeander frieze between bands with added red bands, perhaps lined in white; below, animal frieze, perhaps goat and lion to left; inscription cut on exterior.
Findspot: Excavated/Findspot: Sanctuary of the Dioskouroi (Naukratis), Buried in sand under the west wall of Temenos.
Bibliographic references: Petrie 1886 / Naukratis. Part I., 1884-85 (pl. XXXV, no. 681)
Villing et al 2013-2015 / Naukratis: Greeks in Egypt (GG.420)
